{"word":"ταρβέω","slug":"ταρβέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ταρβέω</b></el> <el>(ταρβέω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:τάρβος'><el>τάρβος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> <i>to be frightened, alarmed, terrified</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <el>τ. φόβῳ</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:— <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to shew fear</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>τὸ ταρβεῖν</el> <i>a state of fear</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>μή με ταρβήσας προδῷς</el> <i>from fear</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>τεταρβηκώς</el> <i>fear-stricken</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to fear, dread</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to stand in awe of, revere</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}